<--Install Node.js-->
https://nodejs.org/en/
node --v (To check Node version) 

<--Install Native Script-->
npm install -g nativescript

<--Install Visual Studio-->
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/?dv=win

<-- Check Installation -->
tns doctor


<--To Create Project in Android -->
1. tns create NativeDemo
 Choose type TypeScript etc

<--Project Path-->
2.cd NativeScriptProjects

<--Go To Project Path-->
2. cd ProjectName

<--To Run Project in Visual Studio-->
3. code .

<--To Run Project in Android -->
4. tns run android -- to run in emulator 
   tns devices -- to get connected devices 
   tns preview -- to preview app on playground 
